description:
Comfortable City of London hotel, steps from St Paul’s

Magnificent view
Club Quarters St. Paul's puts you smack dab in the City of London, across from St Paul’s Cathedral – the view doesn’t get much better than that. City Thameslink station is only a few blocks away, for trains to Gatwick Airport, and St. Paul's Tube Station is just as close.

Follow the river
The hotel is in a historic neighborhood with lots of sights within a mile or so. You can walk over the Millennium Bridge to Shakespeare’s Globe Theatre or the Tate Modern in less than 15 minutes. There are some fantastic river-view restaurants and cafés in this area.

Paris-inspired cuisine
Guests give kudos to Côte restaurant, which delivers good-value French food, such as steak frites and crème caramel. There's free WiFi throughout the hotel, and you can help yourself to purified bottled water.

Making you at home
Clean, comfortable guestrooms are decked out with luxury bedding and linens, workstations with ergonomic chairs, plus TVs with premium channels. By request, you can have a refrigerator, microwave, and exercise equipment delivered to your room.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value: Club Quarters St. Pauls provides an environment that is more apartment building than hotel, and access is restricted to guests only. Most services are complimentary including WiFi throughout the hotel, bottled water, coffee, tea and use of computers and printers. Additional hotel amenities include Côte Brasserie, a French bistro, private Club Living Room with newspaper, magazines, complimentary refreshments, room service, laundry/valet, fitness room and 24-hour Concierge. The property is smoke-free.

DINING.value: Cote Brasserie - Paris bistro-inspired restaurant. Features simple and freshly prepared French fare. Menu includes such items as steak frites, tuna nicoise, moules marinieres, duck confit, and corn-fed chicken. French regional wines available.

GOLD.value: If you’re looking for a great location to soak up London’s historic sights, Club Quarters St. Paul's should be on your short list. Across from St Paul’s Cathedral in the City of London, you can walk over the Millennium Bridge to Shakespeare’s Globe Theatre or the Tate Modern in less than 15 minutes. Guests are impressed by services such as free WiFi and help-yourself bottled water.

At the end of the day…
Our guests love Club Quarters St. Paul's for its excellent location with views of the iconic cathedral dome. They highlight the friendly staff and clean, comfortable rooms. Free WiFi is also a hit.

ROOM_FEATURE.value: Club Quarters St. Pauls offers a fantastic location, putting you just a 5-minute walk from St. Paul's Cathedral and London Stock Exchange. The restaurant is the perfect spot for a bite to eat, and after visiting the fitness center for a workout, you can unwind with a drink at the bar/lounge. Rooms at this upscale hotel offer up nice touches like iPod docks and premium bedding, along with flat-screen TVs and room service.
